description:
File: rust/lichen-gateway/src/aprs_is.rs:256-259

Issue: The recv() method returns None when it encounters a server comment (line starting with #):
    if line.starts_with('#') {
        return Ok(None);
    }

This treats server comments the same as EOF or timeout. Callers cannot distinguish between 'no packet available' and 'server sent a comment we skipped'.

More importantly, if the server sends multiple comments in a row (common after login), the caller would need to call recv() multiple times to get the first real packet.

Suggestion: Change to loop internally to skip comments and return the first real packet, or add a separate return variant to indicate 'comment skipped, try again'.
